==English==

===Etymology===
from Middle English ''[[streit]]'', from Old French ''[[estreit]]'' (modern form [[étroit]])

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪt|-eɪt]]
====Homophones====
*[[straight]]

===Adjective===
'''strait'''

# {{archaic}} narrow
#:''To follow the strait and narrow''

====Usage notes====
The adjective is often confused with ''[[straight]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{geography}} A narrow channel of water
#:''The '''Strait''' of Gibraltar''
#A difficult position (often used in plural)
#:''To be in dire '''straits'''''

